nresult = round((first_k + last_k) / 2, 4)\nprint(f\"{result:.4f}\")", "reason": "Rewrote the script to use the sandbox file paths, load the climate sheet with the correct skipped metadata rows, identify Malta via the radiocarbon regional dataset, interpolate the Potassium K values at the first and last Malta years, average them, round to 4 decimals, and print the result."}) [toolUseId=call_uascJdglVjK0u9IHPr6AwSOp]
